Day 9: SQL – Joins

Topic:
SQL Joins and Table Relationships

Learning Objectives:

Understand how joins are used to combine data from multiple tables
Learn different types of joins: INNER JOIN, LEFT JOIN, RIGHT JOIN, FULL OUTER JOIN, and CROSS JOIN
Understand how relationships between tables work using keys
Learn practical use cases of joins in relational databases

Activities / Deliverables:

Write and execute 10 JOIN queries on a 3-table schema
Practice retrieving related data from multiple tables
Compare results of different join types
Visualize and draw join result sets on paper or diagrams
Understand how missing and matching records appear in joins

Tools / Tech:

MySQL 8
